This paper deals with the performance analysis of IoT networks with grant-free radio access, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also considers the impact of coexisting competing radio access technologies on the system performance, which falls under the category of control and systems engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the expected battery lifetime, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.NI and cs.IT, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.CR.
